  "body": "Geth version: 1.5.9-stable-a07539fb (ubuntu xenial ppa:ethereum/ethereum)\r\nOS & Version: ubuntu xenial\r\n\r\n8Gb ram, entire for blockchain (ext4 data=writeback tested too) 3tb hdd toshuba 5600rpm, \r\n\r\natop: DSK | sdd | busy 101% |  read 6760 |write 1406 | KiB/r 52 | KiB/w 244 | MBr/s 5.73  |MBw/s 5.60| avq     2.79 avio 7.27 ms |\r\n\r\n~30sec per block, too slow (924540 blocks would downloaded in 1 year)\r\n\r\np.s. when used faster cpu,  ssd and 10Gb ram, also tested --cache 1024/8192, - speed increased 4x max, too slow yet\r\nexample log http://pastebin.com/nxd7mKLa\r\n\r\nupd. using bcache with 51Gb ssd cache, --block=4k, sequential_cutoff=0, congested_read_threshold_us=0, congested_write_threshold_us=0 (~70mb/s cache load) give to me good result - **6.57 seconds per block** - ~3 month\r\n",
